parameters: Clea: So, is it okay if I come around evening?
Mage Relm: No, it doesn't take that long.

Clea: Aside from the procedures, there's also the matter of
greetings, right?
Thief Nora: ...I can hardly hear anyone's voice.

Mage Relm: The Magic Academy gathers geniuses from all over
the empire, and each of them is immersed in research every
day for their own achievements.

Mage Relm: Unfortunately, no one here understands my genius,
whether or not the relationships here are useful.

Mage Relm: I will go report to the Archmage. Please wait for
me in my research lab on this floor.
Thief Nora: Relm-san, you seemed lonely.

Clea: Let's find Relm-san's room, where I can imagine her
life here.

\CL Area Liberation\c[18]\CL Kanonas Region/Magic Academy
Front\c[0]
Clea: It seems like this is the place.

Nora the Thief: Look, there are a tremendous number of books
here!
Clea: As expected of a researcher, I suppose.
Male Researcher: Oh, be careful not to touch Relm's books.

Researcher Dokusa: Excuse me, I am a researcher at Dokusa
Magic Academy and a colleague of Relm-kun.

Clea: Thank you very much, Adventurer's Guild. I am Clea
from Ftera.

Researcher Dokusa: Adventurer's Guild... I see, so it seems
the rumors were true after all.
Mage Relm: Ugh, as I thought, they won't release the seal.

Mage Relm: D-Dokusa-san! Please don't enter my room without
permission!

Researcher Dokusa: It's impolite to do as you please. Aren't
we comrades who stand against the conspiracy of the world
together?

Mage Relm: Please don't make me your comrade without
permission.

Researcher Dokusa: I see, so you don't want to involve me.
But rest assured... I am here with determination!
Clea: Is this strange person your friend?

Mage Relm: No, that's not right... Please don't treat me the
same. I'll temporarily leave this place, so please take care
of it, okay?

Researcher Dokusa: I see, so you're taking the initiative to
resolve this. As expected of the assistant candidate No. 3
that I had high hopes for!
Mage Relm: Alright, everyone, let's go.

Researcher Dokusa: How are we going to manage the books
here?

Researcher Dokusa: This should be your treasure, so how
should we manage it during our journey... Hm, I wonder what
to do?

Mage Relm: Sigh... What do you intend to make me do this
time?

Researcher Dokusa: As expected, you catch on quickly. I'll
explain the details in my room, so come over when you're
ready.
Mage Relm: I'm sorry for getting you involved.
Clea: What exactly is your relationship?

Mage Relm: She's a person who is doing research on the
mysteries and conspiracies of the world, which I don't
really understand.

Mage Relm: She's a troublesome person who seems to have
caught wind of my purpose in creating grimoires and keeps
giving me strange requests...
Thief Nora: B-But she didn't seem like a bad person.

Mage Relm: At the very least, she's not a bad person, which
is why it's difficult to deal with her, you know.
Clea: Understood, let's go accept the request.

Researcher Dokusa: I'm glad you came! You will fulfill my
request and in return, you will manage the books.

Mage Relm: There's no problem with those conditions. So,
what is the content of the request?

Researcher Dokusa: There have been multiple incidents of
people being attacked in the Oros region.

Clea: Isn't that under the jurisdiction of the Imperial
Guards?

Researcher Dokusa: Normally, the people who were attacked
claim to have seen beastmen.

Researcher Dokusa: How about it? Can you smell something
suspicious? I believe there is a massive conspiracy behind
this incident--
Mage Relm: Long talks are fine! So, where should we head to?

Researcher Dokusa: First, I want you to go to the Pose Mine
in the Oros region. Please gather information about the
miners who were attacked there.

Researcher Dokusa: The purpose is to solve this incident. I
pray for your success!

Researcher Dokusa: It seems like the situation has been
resolved safely. As expected of the assistant candidate
number 3 that I had high hopes for!

Mage Relm: Yes, yes, I'll leave the book management to me in
place of me.

Researcher Dokusa: Leave it to me! You can trust me when it
comes to that kind of technology, right?
Mage Relm: Well, yeah, to some extent.

Researcher Dokusa: When the time comes to deal with various
conspiracies that need to be resolved, I will contact the
Adventurer's Guild!

Clea: Should I return the equipment I collected during the
request?

Researcher Dokusa: No, I want you to accept it as a small
token of gratitude, as I believe you can make better use of
it.
Clea: Understood, thank you very much.

Researcher Dokusa: I will prepare a bulletin board here
where requests like this one will gather, so please feel
free to accept any requests!

Researcher Dokusa: Well then, I'll go back to my research! I
pray that both adventure and research will go well!
実績 真理の探求者

Researcher Dokusa: Oh, it's you guys! I'm properly managing
Relm-kun's books.
Clea: I came here today to discuss something.
Researcher Dokusa: Hmm, let me hear it.

Mage Relm: So, it seems they want to use crystals to make a
giant ship float.

Mage Relm: I know it's impossible, but do you have any good
ideas?

Researcher Dokusa: During the war with Tarasa, the Imperial
Army, which is not good at naval battles, came up with a
certain strategy.

Researcher Dokusa: It's a strategy to avoid battles at sea
and send a large number of troops to the mainland of Tarasa
for ground warfare.

Researcher Dokusa: I know the core members of this plan,
which involves using airships to transport soldiers.
Clea: Can you tell us about that person?

Researcher Dokusa: That is possible! It is also a request
from Assistant Candidate No. 3 and their friends.

Researcher Dokusa: However, there is a condition for the
exchange!

Mage Relm: Sigh, what kind of troublesome task are you
planning to burden us with this time?

Researcher Dokusa: Actually, I received a special
consultation related to magic from a man named Cors from
Mucos.

Priestess Sophia: It feels like the Empire is quite small,
doesn't it?

Researcher Dokusa: If you know, that's convenient! Please
ask Cors himself for more details!

Researcher Dokusa: I will proceed with the preparations for
the airship. Please come back once the issue in Mucos is
resolved!

Researcher Dokusa: Oh, you're back! Did you settle the
matter with Myukosu?
Clea: Yes, it has been resolved safely.

Researcher Dokusa: Great! She used to be a person who
researched airships...

Researcher Dokusa: He is a man named Karosu who belongs to
the Magic Academy.
Mage Relm: Karosu... Ah, the research on magical tools!

Researcher Dokusa: That's right! Infusing magic power into
crystals and controlling them is his area of expertise.

Researcher Dokusa: I would like you all to try negotiating
with him as well.

Mage Relm: Sigh... From that feeling, it seems like the
negotiations aren't finished yet.
Clea: Understood, let's go meet Mr. Karosu.
Clea: Let's search for Relm's room.

Mage Relm: It seems like my books are safe! Dokusa-san may
be eccentric, but we have to acknowledge their management
skills.
Mage Relm: I'm certain it was around here somewhere...

Researcher Dokusa: Isn't it Assistant Candidate No. 3 and
the others! Have you come today to unravel the mysteries of
the world again?

Clea: I'm here today regarding a request from the Imperial
Army.

Researcher Dokusa: I see, you guys are quite versatile! If
you have some free time, I would like your cooperation with
something.

Mage Relm: Cooperation... we're already being used and we're
not free either, you know!
Researcher Dokusa: Please... it's a serious matter.

Researcher Dokusa: It's fine to do it after your current
job. I've already made a request to the Adventurer's Guild,
so please.

Mage Relm: I've never seen Dokusa-san with such a serious
expression before.
Clea: Do you know where it is?

Mage Relm: That's right... um... in the Oros region... ah, I
found it!
Mage Relm: There is a place related to the demon Yuan.
Clea: Well then, we're going out into the town.

Mage Relm: Thank you for your consideration! I need to
decipher the foolish grimoire for the sake of humanity.

Mage Relm (The condition of the grimoire is quite bad... We
need to carefully open the pages...)

Mage Relm: Alright, it seems like the contents are safe...
This is a magic circle.

Mage Relm (There should be an important secret hidden in
this grimoire that I felt a strong magical power from at
that time--)
Would you like to skip the adult scene?

Mage Relm: I had a terrible experience... but I definitely
felt the power of the grimoire.

Mage Relm: It's unfortunate that it's not a genuine foolish
grimoire, but there's no doubt that it's some kind of
special grimoire.

Mage Relm: Th-this is... resentment... hatred...
loneliness... It's incredible... The magic circle is
constructed by the resentment of the person who wrote it.

Mage Relm: The true form of this much resentment... is... a
virgin? Ridiculed... even my parents cried... I hate the
world.

Mage Relm: Ahaha... Ahahahaha! It's definitely real! A book
written by a genuine fool!

Mage Relm: Ah, I want to burn it! But damaging the book goes
against my beliefs...!

Researcher Dokusa: You're making a lot of noise, Relm-kun!
Have you finally realized the conspiracy of the world?

Mage Relm: I just touched the darkness of the world. If
you'd like, I can give you this grimoire.

Researcher Dokusa: To think you would let go of the book!
Hahaha, tomorrow, the sky might be filled with dragons!
Mage Relm: Sigh... I'll go, okay?

Researcher Dokusa: I wish you good luck! I'm looking forward
to an excellent report.

Researcher Dokusa: When the time comes for the world's
conspiracy that awaits me, I will ask for your assistance!

Researcher Dokusa: Until then, please familiarize yourself
with this bulletin board.

Researcher Dokusa: You guys keep coming to me with
unreasonable requests, I don't have any time to conduct my
own research!

Mage Relm: Is this a request to find someone...? You should
just ask the city guards for something like this.
Researcher Dokusa: It's not such a simple matter, you know!
Mage Relm: D-Don't suddenly appear like that!
Clea: Is there a reason for this?

Researcher Dokusa: Crystals that seal magic... Sometimes
they contain unimaginable things.

Researcher Dokusa: Research was conducted to counter the
powerful Wald warriors during the First Wald War era.
Mage Relm: Could it be about the Tears of Lupid?!

Researcher Dokusa: Let's give this to Relm-kun. He should be
able to nullify the magical effects of Lupid.

Researcher Dokusa: The shame of the Magic Academy! Please
rescue the victims of demonic research achievements!
Clea: What are the Tears of Lupid?

Mage Relm: It is the result of an experiment that uses the
magic of the demon Lupid, who can transform into a beast, to
enhance the body.

Mage Relm: The results were terrible, it seems. It is said
that it attacked indiscriminately, regardless of friend or
foe.

Mage Relm: The Academy tried to cover up the truth, but in
the end, it was resolved by the priests of the Terios
Church.

Mage Relm: I'll take care of cleaning up the mess left by
the past mages. As an active and talented mage, I will
resolve it thoroughly!
実績 ヴァルト地方発見

parameters:
Clea: Defeating a giant snake... That will require some
skill.
Mage Relm: The place is... the town of medicine, Medicina!?

Mage Relm: I can't believe a place like this would have a
giant snake, hmm...
Clea: First, let's meet the client.

\CL Area Liberation\c[18]\CL Kanonas Region/Medicina, the
Town of Medicine\c[0]

Male Junior Sorcerer: Um... could you please not disturb my
research on alchemy?

Male Junior Sorcerer: Are you still not giving up on the
dragon? We are seekers of magic, not rare beast hunters.

Male Junior Sorcerer: I can't believe dragons actually
exist...! The academy is buzzing with rumors about you.

Female Intermediate Mage: In the records of the Tarasa Naval
Battle, there are records of large ships... and then...

Intermediate-level female magician: Oh, long time no see. I
haven't seen you around lately, so I thought you got fired.

Intermediate female mage: I heard about the dragon. I'm
looking forward to seeing what you will accomplish from now
on.

Magic Academy Teacher: We're in the middle of class, please
leave.

Magic Academy Teacher: This lecture is meaningless to you.
Come back when we have a higher-level lecture.

Apprentice Researcher: I don't understand at all... I was a
prodigy in my hometown...

Apprentice Researcher: The level is too high... ugh... I
feel like giving up...

Magic Academy Librarian: Welcome to the Magic Academy.
Please refrain from touching the books without permission.

Magic Academy Librarian: Please make sure to return the
books you've read! Relm-san's room is not a library!

Magic Academy Librarian: I heard about the dragon
subjugation! But that doesn't excuse you from not returning
the books!

Magic Academy Librarian: Relm-san! More than 20 books have
already exceeded the due date for return!

Mage Relm: I apologize for that, but were there any books
related to heroes in the Magic Academy?

Magic Academy Librarian: There aren't many, as the
embellished fairy tales are not needed in the Academy.
Archmage: I see, gathering good breasts and good buttocks...

Archmage: Oh my, sorry to bother you, but could you come to
my room?

Archmage: I would like to hear a little bit about the
conversation you were having.
Clea: They might be concerned about this investigation.

Mage Relm: I don't think that's the case. After all, it's a
request from the person who is being viewed as a threat.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置

Magic Academy Librarian: I heard about the dragon
subjugation! But that doesn't excuse you from returning the
books!

Magic Academy Researcher: Please contact someone else for
your business. I am busy with my research and do not have
time.

Mage Tatunoko: What is it? Are you interested in my
research?

Mage Tatsumoko: T-This is...!? Even though I have a wife,
I-I can't resist your charm!

Mage Tatsumoko: T-This is...!? It's my treasured possession,
but... I want you to have it.

Mage Tatsunoko: I will create controllable tentacles
someday! When I succeed... cough cough... it's just a
mutter.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置

Mage Relm: The book of potions... If I study this content, I
might be able to figure something out...

Mage Relm: I will lock myself in the potion room and
definitely complete the request, so please wait!

Clea: I understand. Please make sure not to push yourself
too hard.
Mage Relm: Hehe, I'll finish it right away and show you!
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置

events.name: クエストアイコン『EV033 【189】悩める薬師1-3』

parameters:
Mage Relm: I need some kind of clue... information to stop
the advance of the monsters...

Intermediate male mage: You're telling quite an interesting
story. Transformations are my research subject. Could you
tell me more in detail?

Intermediate male mage: Ahahaha, that's quite an interesting
joke!

Mage Relm: This is no laughing matter! We are seriously
investigating here!

Intermediate male mage: It's impossible to transform
creatures as advanced as humans. As a mage, you should
understand that better than anyone, right?

Mage Relm: Grrr... That may be true, but do you know
anything, anything at all, that could help us!?

Intermediate male mage: Hmm... if it's a legend, I have
heard a story from the time when Valt was not part of the
Empire yet.

Intermediate male mage: I heard a story that there were
monsters among the warriors of Valt. These monsters not only
attacked the Imperial soldiers, but also indiscriminately
attacked others.
Clea: We're completely stuck, aren't we?

Mage Relm: There is definitely some kind of magic involved!
It is likely related to lost magic!

Thief Nora: If it's lost magic, that means there's no way to
investigate it, right...?

Clea: It seems like we have no choice but to rely on Sophia-
san after all.

Priestess Sophia: I understand that this is an emergency
situation, but even if I'm called a savior, I don't know
what I should do.

Priestess Sophia: My mentor... as a priestess... is Eleo-
chan, Sister Eleo.

Clea: Let's go meet Sister Eleo. She should definitely be
willing to help us.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置

events.name: EV047クリスタルの中の助手

parameters:
Researcher Dokusa: I'm glad you came. I want to share the
deciphered code with you.

Researcher Dokusa: Albus left two clues. First, an encrypted
invitation, and second, a crystal.

Researcher Dokusa: If you decipher the code, this should be
a familiar sight to Assistant Candidate No. 3.

Mage Relm: It's a demon's magic circle, right? It belongs to
Refgaria, Guaipezo, and Yuan.

Researcher Dokusa: I don't think Albus left these two things
without any reason.

Researcher Dokusa: I feel challenged by the message 'Show me
that you have arrived' as if it's some kind of provocation.

Mage Relm: Clea-san, do you remember? We fought against the
person who turned into a beastman deep in the forest of
Refgaria.

Clea: I remember it well. It was when I first came to the
academy.

Mage Relm: There should have been a shrine deep in the
forest of Refgaria...

Mage Relm: There was a pedestal there. Maybe something will
happen if we place the crystal on it.

Researcher Dokusa: First, I'll entrust you with the
invitation and the crystal... First, please head towards the
forest of Refgaria.
Mage Relm: I will prove that my deduction is correct!
Researcher Dokusa: Just to let you know--

Mage Relm: Don't worry, I'm not alone, so everything will be
fine!

Researcher Dokusa: That's right, please find Albus for me,
I'm counting on you.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置
Mage Relm: Finally, I've received a personal summons too...!

Clea: Pulse-san... You're the one who helped us during the
time of the mage Lapis, right?

Mage Relm: It seems they are providing funding to
exceptional mages. Hehehe, it's quite impressive that
they've recognized my genius!

Mage Relm: Let's go meet them right away! This will bring me
one step closer to becoming an Archmage!
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置
Mage Relm: Is this a request from the nobleman Mr. Crow?

Mage Relm: He is a nobleman who supports the Magic Academy
and conducts independent research on magic.

Mage Relm: Although my talent in magic is lacking, I know
the location of the mansion, so I will guide you.
Clea: Nice to meet you. Please take care of me.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置

\CL Area Liberation\c[18]\CL Kanonas Region / Researcher's
Mansion\c[0]
Clea: It seems like a search request for a missing person.

Priestess Sophia: When it involves a merchant guild, I can't
help but be suspicious. There are many who turn into
villains when money is involved.
Clea: First, let's try to contact the client.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置

other herbs, we might be able to amplify its effects...

Mage Relm: Combining it with magic... It wouldn't make sense

Mage Relm: W-What's with the sudden loud voice?
